narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned more about multivariable calculus and 3d space in general.
I developed my Multivariable skills and self learning.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course is taught at a bit too difficult a level for the advertised audience. It should include the same concepts, but easier questions.
Its great in that its fast paced, very organized (following the textbook), the flipped classroom method with the videos was really effective
There is a lot too be self taught in this class otherwise it is difficult to follow although that is one of the parts I like.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this if you are going into a stem field and it is a requirement. Otherwise, do not hurt yourself.
I would. Its hard but doable and made me much more confident in math.
Yes, I think this class is quite essential.
Unless they need it for their major, there are better options
